The paper deals with the use of M-estimators in generalized linear regression models in high dimensional settings, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a new analysis framework for iterative hard thresholding methods, which are widely used in this context. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also deals with sparse regression and low-rank matrix recovery, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), respectively.
